WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.157
Diagnosis relies on troponin elevation, ECG

00:00:03.157 --> 00:00:06.313
changes including ST segment abnormalities, elevated

00:00:06.313 --> 00:00:09.470
B-type natriuretic peptide, and cardiac imaging.

00:00:09.470 --> 00:00:12.100
Echocardiography demonstrates left ventricular dysfunction.

00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:15.257
Cardiac MRI shows myocardial inflammation and

00:00:15.257 --> 00:00:16.309
scar distribution.

00:00:16.309 --> 00:00:19.465
Management is primarily supportive with guideline-directed

00:00:19.465 --> 00:00:22.096
medical therapy for heart failure.

00:00:22.096 --> 00:00:25.252
Severe, fulminant cases may require mechanical

00:00:25.252 --> 00:00:27.357
circulatory support or transplantation.

00:00:27.357 --> 00:00:30.513
Long-term follow-up with serial imaging and

00:00:30.513 --> 00:00:33.670
risk stratification is essential given the

00:00:33.670 --> 00:00:36.300
potential for progression to cardiomyopathy.
